column5: Well there were several big perch around but there were no walleye found.  We stayed on the one rod side of the ferry, marked little.  Note: we are not walleye guys.  There were a few other boats but they all left before dark...thats the end for the skunky report.  forrest
still ,  it's always great to be on the water  I hope they turn on soon

usually after halloween, picton starts heating up, been there with ice on the water and having heaters to warm up your hands before christmas, it's cold but worth it, lots of fish to be had when the weather gets colder and alot of fun cheers.
Just keep at it.... I'm sure you'll find them sooner than later Leechman
Was there on Saturday other side of the ferry they have lock jaw  Rob

sounds like a great day to me,i was out there myself,dropped my 8 day old camera over board in 97' of water,try telling that one to the wife   .  oh head east......way east..then north west   Hawg Hunter
